Skills and Abilities
Ninja abilities unlock at their listed <guild level> and begin at 70%
reliability. A failed reliability roll costs one fifth of the ability's
spell-point cost, but does not consume its item, start its cooldown, or add
a combo piece.

Ninja rank is separate from guild level. Every rank after rank 1 earns one
training session. Use <practice> to spend a session and improve one ability
by 5%, up to 100%. Rank costs 250 guild XP (GXP) each time. Valid skill
attempts, completed combos, and qualifying combat kills award GXP. An NPC ten
or more levels below you is too weak to grant battle GXP. Use <nskills> to
review rank, GXP, sessions, marks, and reliability.

Many offensive techniques also add a piece to the Ninja combo system.
When enough recent pieces are present, the wraps may release a special
combat sequence. See <ninhelp combo> for details.
